Reasoning: The paper deals with graph coloring problems, which are typically studied in the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of graph classes and their properties, which falls under the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of computing the very strong rainbow connection number, which is a problem in Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
